 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-SPEC-002: Implement DocumentedResidual type for bilateral fixpoint tracking. PROBLEM: bilateral.rs has no DocumentedResidual type. Gaps detected by forward_scan/backward_scan are returned in ScanResult but never persisted across cycles. The bilateral loop cannot reach fixpoint because there is no mechanism to document unresolvable divergence. F(S) cannot distinguish 'no divergence' from 'all divergence documented'. SOLUTION: (1) Add DocumentedResidual struct {gap_id, reason, first_detected_cycle, acknowledged_by}. (2) Persist as datoms between bilateral cycles. (3) Track gap age. (4) After 1 cycle, require documentation or F(S).D takes penalty. VERIFICATION: (1) proptest: after documenting all residuals, F(S) fixpoint reached. (2) Unit test: undocumented gap persisting > 1 cycle reduces F(S).D. DEPENDS-ON: None. INTERACTS-WITH: W0-004 (F(S) monotonicity scope), W2-007 (Phi accuracy)."
